p: We used 20 envelope sequences (1,485 nucleotides) of DENV-1 isolates obtained from patients in SJRP, from 2008 to 2012, for the phylogenetic analyses. The results indicated that the isolates were subdivided into two lineages within genotype V. Isolates 59/2011, 287/2011, 354/2011, 395/2011, 422/2011, 430/2011, 437/2011, 442/2011, 492/2012 and 516/2012 were grouped within one lineage previously called L1 or lineage II [ 13, 18] the most recent common ancestor (MRCA) for those species dates back to approximately 2008 (95% BCI = 2006–2009). Ten isolates from SJRP were grouped in another lineage, previously called L6 or lineage I [ 13, 18]: 365/2008, 09/2009, 88/2010, 64/2011, 205/2011, 384/2011, 387/2011, 484/2012, 531/2012 and 552/2012. These isolates share an MRCA from approximately 2007 (2006–2008) ( Fig 1A).
